</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org9751b34" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org9751b34">Cost of open source software</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org9751b34">
<p>
It is generally freely available for downloading. So aquisition cost is
very low or free. But there are other costs involved in running any software
whehter open source or propiteary there are other costs involved such as
tech support, training, adminstration, Maintanance and customization.
</p>

<p>
Some Open Source Licenses allow developers to sell their software.
But it may require them to release the source when they do. This would
allow any user to compile and run the code.  Many companies in the
open source industry build their businesses on providing service and
support to the software they provide. They make money helping others
install use and troubleshoot rather then selling the software
directly.
</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
